Add a comprehensive CLI tool to the Forever library. Create a `bin/forever.js` executable (with a `#!/usr/bin/env node` shebang) that provides a command-line interface for using Forever utilities. Requirements: 1) A `validate` command that accepts JSON input via stdin or a file flag and validates it against a schema file. 2) A `benchmark` command that runs the benchmark suite from the `benchmarks/` directory and prints results to stdout in either table or JSON format (selectable via a `--format` flag). 3) A `plugin list` sub-command that lists all built-in plugins. 4) Parse CLI arguments manually using `process.argv` (no third-party argument parsers). 5) Provide `--help` output for all commands. 6) Add a `"bin"` entry to `package.json` pointing to `bin/forever.js`. 7) Write tests in `tests/cli.test.js` that spawn the CLI as a child process and assert stdout/stderr output and exit codes.